WORK

2020: Europe's COVID-19 Spending Spree Unmasked

A good part of 2020, I worked with the OCCRP on collecting and analysing European COVID-19 public tender data. We have collected 21 billion euros worth of tender data from 37 countries. Article: https://www.occrp.org/en/coronavirus/europes-covid-19-spending-spree-unmasked OpenContracting blog: https://www.open-contracting.org/2021/02/04/unmasking-emergency-procurement-how-we-published-37000-european-covid-19-related-tenders/ Github repository: https://github.com/occrp/COVID-19-spending-2020

2020: Lecturer at masters in Investigative Journalism

In the autumn 2020 I was part of the team teaching data skills to master students at the University of Gothenburg. Website: https://www.gu.se/en/study-gothenburg/masters-programme-in-investigative-journalism-s2jou

2014-2020 Dataharvest conference

Active not only as a participant, but also HackDay coordinator and data skills trainer. In 2020 I had the honors to coordinate and moderate all the data skills sessions on a 3 month long digital conference.

2019: Pointer

In 2019 I worked with the largest data team in the contemporary Dutch media landscape: Pointer. My favourite stories include effects of nutrient pollution on endangered birds (https://pointer.kro-ncrv.nl/zeldzame-vogels-in-gevaar-door-stikstofvervuiling), 2 part series on the impossible Dutch FOIA law (https://pointer.kro-ncrv.nl/een-overheidsdocument-aangevraagd-daar-moet-je-soms-jaren-op-wachten), and the Dutch water bodies (https://pointer.kro-ncrv.nl/de-waterschappen-kosten-jaarlijks-drie-miljard-en-vooral-jij-betaalt-die-rekening) [image by Tijmen Snelderwaard]

2014-2018: OneWorld

Worked as data journalist for a small Dutch magazine focused on sustainability and human rights. Stories I wrote in the last year of working there would include one on CO2 compensation from flying by giving cooking stoves to families in Africa (https://www.oneworld.nl/lezen/klimaat/klimaatonrecht/laat-klm-nou-echt-een-ghanese-familie-onze-co2uitstoot-compenseren/) and how Dutch restaurants are not wheelchair friendly (https://www.oneworld.nl/lezen/achtergrond/u-kunt-hier-niet-naar-de-wc/)
